to the editor as an educator and a computer user i am distressed at the revolution in education brought about by laptop computers front page march 26 your article opened with an account of a wake forest university student who coped with a boring economics lecture by checking stock prices and sports scores on his laptop how will he manage to get through boring meetings in the work world twenty years ago computer makers convinced many school boards that calculators were an excellent teaching tool now many young adults ca n't do simple arithmetic without a calculator with the widespread use of laptops we face the prospect of a generation unable to look up a reference in a book or to take notes with pen and pad education should hardly be making students more dependent on the latest gadgets lewis zimmerman east meadow ny march 26 2000

